[08:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to MIDI. There is a pop-up window that for whatever reason you can\'t see here, but it allows you to choose the conversion model and what the language of the model is. In this case, I\'m using version two, which is their latest model, and I\'m choosing the English language, and clicking on convert. And'

[09:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'now it\'s looking at all of the vocal information and converting each of my notes into MIDI notes complete with modulation and pitchbend, and it reads the lyrics. And down here in the editor window, you have access to the lyrics. So, if you want to change them'

[09:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'completely or fix some that were wrong, you could do that here just by clicking on them and typing and it will fill in the notes automatically provided the syllables line up. If not, you can certainly go in there and edit all these. If you want to go into more detail on how this editor works, all the'

[09:31] [scene:talk]
